			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Mercury is often present alongside zinc, cadmium, silver, carbon, and gold, as mercuric chloride, sulfides, and oxides. All three forms of mercury are considered dangerous in water; however, organic mercury is easily absorbed by the human body, making it more toxic than inorganic mercury compounds. Mercury is also found in two positively charged, or cationic, states, Hg2+ (mercuric) and Hg1+(mercurous).</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">汞通常以氯化汞、硫化物和氧化物的形式与锌、镉、银、碳和金同时存在。所有这三种形式的汞在水中都被认为是危险的；但是，有机汞很容易被人体吸收，因此它比无机汞化合物毒性更大。汞还以两种带正电荷或阳离子的状态存在，即 Hg2+（亚汞）和 Hg1+（亚汞）。</common:generalComment>
